The paper discusses the development of a cross-blockchain protocol for creating a unified ecosystem of multiple networks, which involves addressing issues related to scalability, digital identity, and immutability. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
